  "texts": [
    "Proposition 5.",
    "Let us consider the original kinetic model (13) in the presence of opinion leaders, with G ≡ 1, and suppose that the initial distribution f in (A, w) has a compact support.",
    "Then, the average opinion of the population m w (t) converges toward the average opinion of the leaders µ ℓ, in the limit t → +∞.Proof.",
    "Since the interactions agent-agent preserve the average opinion (see Subsection 2.2), we can reduce our study to the sole interactions agent-leader.",
    "As pointed out at the beginning of Subsection 4.1, only three scenarios are possible:• if a p + a ℓ belongs to case (i), then for large times all agents become active;• if a p + a ℓ belongs to case (iii), then for large times all agents become inactive;• if a p + a ℓ belongs to case (ii), then for large times there are only active agents and inactive agents (under the realistic assumption that the initial number of agents with an activity level A * ∈ (-γ, γ), defined as the unique solution to Ā(ω p +ω ℓ)+2ε-a p -a ℓ = 0, is negligible).In particular, in all three cases the mass fractions of the population are definitely constant."
  ],
